0conflict.%20Overstay%20penalties%20will%20be%20waived%20for%20those%20delayed%20until%20February%2028.%20Exit%20permits%20will%20be%20issued%20free%20of%20charge.%20Temporary%20Landing%20Permits%20are%20also%20being%20granted%20to%20diverted%20flights.%20This%20comes%20as%20the%20conflict%20escalates%2C%20impacting%20regional%20travel%20and%20energy%20supplies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20BUSINESS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meta%20is%20weighing%20major%20layoffs%20as%20it%20pours%20billions%20into%20AI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224873%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Meta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69a74cb4d3e2f1aef369ecda%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223349%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMeta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%3Cp%3EWally%20Skalij%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMeta%20is%20preparing%20for%20possible%20layoffs%2C%20with%20some%20managers%20asked%20to%20draw%20up%20cost-cutting%20plans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20cuts%20could%20come%20as%20Meta%20ramps%20up%20spending%20on%20AI%20infrastructure%20and%20talent.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20potential%20cuts%20would%20underscore%20how%20aggressively%20Big%20Tech%20is%20trimming%20head%20count%20to%20finance%20the%20AI%20boom.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20is%20gearing%20up%20for%20possible%20layoffs%20as%20it%20pours%20billions%20into%20AI%2C%20two%20senior%20employees%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sources%20said%20that%20some%20managers%20have%20been%20asked%20to%20prepare%20cost-cutting%20plans%20but%20were%20not%20told%20their%20scope%20or%20timing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReuters%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fworld-at-work%2Fmeta-planning-sweeping-layoffs-ai-costs-mount-2026-03-14%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20potential%20layoffs%20on%20Friday%2C%20said%20that%20up%20to%2020%25%20of%20Meta%20employees%20could%20be%20let%20go.%20As%20of%20the%20end%20of%202025%2C%20Meta%20employed%20nearly%2079%2C000%20people%2C%20so%20a%20potential%20cut%20of%2020%25%20would%20mean%20roughly%2016%2C000%20jobs%20eliminated.%20That%20would%20be%20Meta's%20most%20significant%20reduction%20since%202022%2C%20when%20it%20cut%2011%2C000%20jobs%2C%20and%202023%2C%20when%20it%20cut%20another%2010%2C000.%20In%20January%2C%20Meta%20laid%20off%201%2C500%20people%20in%20its%20Reality%20Labs%20division.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20company's%20thinking%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20cuts%20could%20come%20as%20soon%20as%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20speculative%20reporting%20about%20theoretical%20approaches%2C%26quot%3B%20Meta%20spokesperson%20Andy%20Stone%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Meta%20moves%20forward%20with%20these%20cuts%2C%20it%20would%20signal%20a%20broader%20shift%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20as%20companies%20pour%20massive%20amounts%20of%20capital%20into%20AI%20infrastructure%20and%20talent%20while%20trimming%20the%20workforces%20that%20once%20powered%20their%20growth%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20weeks%2C%20Atlassian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatlassian-layoff-global-workforce-attributes-it-to-the-ai-era-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eannounced%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20cut%20roughly%201%2C600%20employees%2C%20or%2010%25%20of%20its%20staff%2C%20tying%20the%20move%20to%20AI%20and%20a%20push%20for%20efficiency.%20Block%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-jack-dorsey-ai-impact-as-block-cuts-layoffs-workforce-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ealso%20slashed%3C%2Fa%3E%20jobs%2C%20with%20CEO%20Jack%20Dorsey%20saying%20new%20AI%20tools%20allow%20companies%20to%20operate%20with%20smaller%20teams%20and%20more%20efficiency.%20These%20cuts%20signal%20a%20new%20strategy%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%3A%20as%20AI%20becomes%20more%20capable%2C%20the%20biggest%20technology%20companies%20are%20betting%20they%20can%20build%20faster%20and%20cheaper%20with%20fewer%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20has%20said%20it%20plans%20to%20invest%20roughly%20%24600%20billion%20to%20build%20out%20data%20centers%20by%202028.%20The%20company%20has%20also%20offered%20pay%20packages%20worth%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20over%20four%20years%20to%20lure%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-escalates-ai-talent-war-with-openai-shengjia-zhao-zuckerberg-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etop%20AI%20researchers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20its%20new%20superintelligence%20team%20led%20by%20former%20Scale%20AI%20CEO%20Alexnadr%20Wang.%20Financing%20those%20bets%2C%20while%20satisfying%20Wall%20Street%2C%20means%20finding%20savings%20elsewhere.%20Head%20count%20is%20the%20most%20obvious%20lever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Meta's%20January%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-q4-earnings-stock-price-ai-capex-live-updates-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eearnings%20call%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20told%20investors%20the%20company%20is%20already%20%26quot%3Belevating%20individual%20contributors%20and%20flattening%20teams.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20he's%20seeing%20%26quot%3Bprojects%20that%20used%20to%20require%20big%20teams%20now%20be%20accomplished%20by%20a%20single%2C%20very%20talented%20person.%26quot%3B%20Last%20week%2C%20Meta%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-new-applied-engineering-team-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreated%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20brand-new%20AI%20engineering%20organization%2C%20where%20teams%20will%20have%20manager-to-employee%20ratios%20of%20up%20to%201%3A50.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20Meta's%20size%2C%20a%2020%25%20reduction%20at%20Meta%20would%20dwarf%20many%20of%20its%20Big%20Tech%20peercuts%20in%20absolute%20terms%2C%20wiping%20out%20more%20jobs%20than%20the%20entire%20head%20count%20of%20many%20midsize%20tech%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta's%20urgency%20around%20AI%20comes%20after%20a%20difficult%20stretch%20for%20its%20in-house%20model%20efforts.%20The%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fllamacon-2025-meta-strived-reassert-ai-leadership-against-rivals-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efaced%20criticism%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20early%20versions%20of%20its%20Llama%204%20models%20produced%20misleading%20benchmark%20results%2C%20and%20it%20ultimately%20shelved%20the%20largest%20version%20of%20that%20model%2C%20called%20Behemoth%2C%20which%20had%20been%20due%20out%20last%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20Superintelligence%20team%20has%20since%20been%20working%20on%20a%20new%20model%20called%20Avocado%20and%20Mango%2C%20which%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2026%2F03%2F12%2Ftechnology%2Fmeta-avocado-ai-model-delayed.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereportedly%3C%2Fa%3E%20fallen%20short%20of%20internal%20expectations%20and%20been%20delayed%20until%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20Pranav%20Dixit%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Apranavdixit%40protonmail.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Epranavdixit%40protonmail.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3Eor%20Signal%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22tel%3A14089059124%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3E1-408-905-9124%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business