0to%20the%20magazine%20pictorial.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bfinest%20boys%20in%20finance%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20whose%20splashy%20magazine%20spread%20last%20week%20was%20the%20talk%20of%20Wall%20Street%20%E2%80%94%20is%20no%20longer%20with%20his%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20PwC%20confirmed%20that%20former%20associate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-four-bankers-pwc-goldman-barclays-interview-magazine-viral-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDemarre%20Johnson%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20%26quot%3Bno%20longer%20an%20employee%20and%20left%20the%20firm%20in%20mid-February.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%20went%20viral%20last%20week%20after%20he%20and%20three%20junior%20bankers%20were%20featured%20in%20designer%20clothing%20in%20an%20Interview%20magazine%20photo%20shoot%20published%20March%204.%20A%20person%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%20said%20his%20departure%20was%20not%20related%20to%20his%20magazine%20appearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2023-year-old%2C%20who%20spoke%20with%20Business%20Insider%20twice%20after%20the%20magazine%20story%2C%20didn't%20comment%20when%20a%20reporter%20reached%20him%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Babson%20College%20graduate%20talked%20to%20Business%20Insider%20last%20week%20about%20being%20chosen%20for%20the%20spread%2C%20saying%20he%20knew%20it%20would%20make%20headlines%20because%20%26quot%3Bcontroversy%20sells.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20initial%20reaction%20was%2C%20'Oh%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20clown%20us%20because%20we%20think%20we're%20pretty%2C'%26quot%3B%20Johnson%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20exactly%20what%20happened.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20photo%20shoot%20generated%20instant%20discourse%20among%20Wall%20Street%20insiders%20who%20took%20to%20social%20media%20to%20vent%20about%20the%20stereotypes%20they%20said%20it%20portrayed%20and%20the%20unofficial%20rules%20it%20broke%20%E2%80%94%20including%20not%20outshining%20your%20bosses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBankers%20buzzed%20about%20whether%20the%20participants%20%E2%80%94%20who%20also%20worked%20at%20Goldman%20Sachs%20and%20Barclays%20%E2%80%94%20got%20approval%20from%20their%20employers%20before%20going%20in%20front%20of%20the%20cameras.%20Goldman%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bmedia%20relations%20did%20not%20approve%20these%20interviews.%26quot%3B%20The%20other%20firms%20didn't%20comment%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%2C%20who%20has%20a%20vibrant%20social%20media%20presence%2C%20said%20on%20Monday%20that%20he's%20been%20careful%20about%20social%20media%20posts%20he's%20made%20about%20his%20job.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20built%20the%20multibillion-dollar%20bank%20business%2C%20I%20would%20hate%20if%20one%20of%20my%20associates%20formed%20my%20company's%20image%20with%20one%20video%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinance-boys-tiktok-generation-old-school-wall-street-goldman-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehe%20told%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20participants%20in%20the%20shoot%20have%20avoided%20the%20spotlight%20since%20its%20release%2C%20but%20Johnson%20reposted%20feedback%20about%20the%20story%20on%20his%20social%20channels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20viral%20on%20twitter%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20one%20post%2C%20with%20four%20crying%20emojis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdemarre-johnson-finest-boys-finance-pwc-interview-magazine-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773434815000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b475b1a7a4f9df67ba563c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdemarre-johnson-finest-boys-finance-pwc-interview-magazine-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Demarre%20Johnson%2C%2023%2C%20and%20three%20others%20went%20viral%20for