%3Cp%3EFOMC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFederal%20Judge%20Boasberg%20dismissed%20subpoenas%20against%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%2C%20citing%20%26quot%3Bzero%20evidence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20an%20unsealed%20ruling%2C%20the%20judge%20said%20the%20evidence%20suggests%20the%20probe%20was%20%26quot%3Bpretextual.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUS%20Attorney%20Pirro%20plans%20to%20appeal%20the%20judge's%20decision%2C%20maintaining%20pressure%20on%20Jerome%20Powell's%20Fed%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EScore%20one%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomists-finance-business-leaders-react-trump-doj-investigation-fed-powell-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJerome%20Powell.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20District%20Judge%20James%20Boasberg%20has%20tossed%20two%20subpoenas%20that%20the%20Justice%20Department%20served%20on%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Board%20of%20Governors%2C%20ending%20%E2%80%94%20for%20now%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffed-chair-jerome-powell-video-statement-leadership-move-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eits%20criminal%20probe%20into%20the%20Fed%20Chair.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20ruling%20unsealed%20on%20Friday%2C%20Boasberg%20said%20the%20subpoenas%20served%20an%20%26quot%3Bimproper%20purpose.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20mountain%20of%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20the%20government%20served%20these%20subpoenas%20on%20the%20board%20to%20pressure%20its%20chair%20into%20voting%20for%20lower%20interest%20rates%20or%20resigning%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote%20in%20the%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20scale%2C%20the%20Government%20has%20produced%20essentially%20zero%20evidence%20to%20suspect%20Chair%20Powell%20of%20a%20crime%2C%26quot%3B%20Boasberg%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BIndeed%2C%20its%20justifications%20are%20so%20thin%20and%20unsubstantiated%20that%20the%20Court%20can%20only%20conclude%20that%20they%20are%20pretextual.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20subpoenas%20sought%20records%20about%20recent%20renovations%20of%20the%20Fed's%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20buildings%20and%20Powell's%20testimony%20before%20the%20Senate%20Banking%20Committee%20in%20June%20about%20those%20renovations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoasberg%20opened%20his%2027-page%20ruling%20with%20a%20July%20Truth%20Social%20from%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20blasting%20Powell%20as%20%26quot%3BTOO%3Cbr%3EANGRY%2C%20TOO%20STUPID%2C%20%26amp%3B%20TOO%20POLITICAL.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20is%20one%20of%20at%20least%20100%20statements%20that%20the%20President%20or%20his%20deputies%20have%20made%20attacking%20the%20Chair%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20and%20pressuring%20him%20to%20lower%20interest%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Attorney%20Jeanine%20Pirro%20blasted%20the%20judge%20and%20said%20the%20Justice%20Department%20would%20appeal%20the%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20the%20judge's%20order%2C%20%26quot%3BJerome%20Powell%20today%20is%20now%20bathed%20in%20immunity%2C%20preventing%20my%20office%20from%20investigating%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%2C%26quot%3B%20Pirro%20told%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPirro's%20statement%20came%20after%20a%20key%20Republican%20lawmaker%2C%20Sen.%20Thom%20Tillis%20of%20North%20Carolina%2C%20reiterated%20his%20opposition%20to%20confirming%20Kevin%20Warsh%20as%20Powell's%20replacement%20until%20the%20criminal%20investigation%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20Powell%20confirmed%20that%20the%20central%20bank%20received%20subpoenas%20in%20an%20extraordinary%20video%20message%20that%20cast%20the%20probe%20as%20retribution%20for%20Powell's%20repeated%20defiance%20of%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20desires%20to%20cut%20interest%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20threat%20of%20criminal%20charges%20is%20a%20consequence%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20setting%20interest%20rates%20based%20on%20our%20best%20assessment%20of%20what%20will%20serve%20the%20public%20rather%20than%20following%20the%20preferences%20of%20the%20president%2C%26quot%3B%20Powell%20said%20in%20the%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20criminal%20investigation%20was%20just%20one%20way%20Trump%20and%20his%20allies%20have%20tried%20to%20pressure%20the%20historically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-weighs-trump-federal-reserve-independence-lisa-cook-powell-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eindependent%20central%20bank.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Trump%20tried%20to%20fire%20Fed%20Gov.%20Lisa%20Cook%20in%20August%202025%2C%20but%20she%20has%20remained%20at%20the%20Fed%20as%20the%20legal%20fight%20unfolds.%20In%20January%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20heard%20oral%20arguments%20in%20that%20case%2C%20where%20justices%20expressed%20skepticism%20about%20the%20White%20House's%20push.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPowell's%20term%20is%20up%20in%20May.%20Trump%20announced%20his%20nomination%20of%20Warsh%2C%20a%20former%20member%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%2C%20last%20month%20and%20formally%20submitted%20it%20to%20the%20Senate%20weeks%20ago.%20Warsh%20has%20spent%20the%20past%20week%20meeting%20with%20lawmakers%2C%20including%20Tillis%2C%20on%20Capitol%20Hill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETillis's%20opposition%20is%20a%20significant%20obstacle%20to%20Warsh's%20confirmation%2C%20given%20that%20he%20sits%20on%20the%20Banking%20Committee%2C%20which%20would%20vote%20on%20Warsh's%20nomination%20before%20a%20potential%20full%20Senate%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20developing%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-tosses-federal-reserve-chair-jerome-powell-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1773431419000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b463f94d65ec517529fe95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22